description:
Six love stories from all corners of the DC Universe! A special one-shot featuring many superheroes in Valentine's Day related stories.

Stories Featured:

  • "Think it Through" starring Catwoman and Batman. Written by Ann Nocenti, illustrated by Emanuela Lupacchino and Jaime Mendoza.
  • "The Lighthouse" starring Aquaman and Mera. Written by Cecil Castellucci, illustrated by Inaki Miranda.
  • "Dreamer" starring Barbara Gordon. Written by Ray Fawkes, illustrated by Julius Gopez.
  • "Seoul Brothers" starring Apollo and Midnighter. Written by Peter Milligan, illustrated by Simon Bisley.
  • "Another Saturday Night" starring Dick Grayson. Written by Kyle Higgins, illustrated by Sanford Greene.
  • "Truth or Dare" starring Superman and Wonder Woman. Written by Andy Diggle, illustrated by Robson Rocha and Julio Ferreira.

Note: Though not technically a The New 52 series, the title occupied the fifty-second spot in the line up during February 2013, where DC only had 51 regular on-going titles published, due to the soon to be launched Constantine starting in March, after the 300th and final issue of Hellblazer in February.

Also inside: 18 Valentine's Day Cards featuring various superheroes.
name: Young Romance: The New 52 Valentine's Day Special

Earth has been populated by thousands of aliens from all over the galaxy. While all the other aliens are aware of their presence, it is a secret only from the Earthlings. Baka, the prince of the planet Dogra, crash lands on Earth and loses his memory. He forcibly moves in with Yukitata Tsuitsui, a first year high school student who had just moved out on his own.
